"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(DISTINCT users.Id)\nFROM users\nJOIN posts ON users.Id = posts.OwnerUserId\nWHERE users.Location = 'United Kingdom'\nAND posts.FavoriteCount >= 4;\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of distinct users located in the United Kingdom whose posts have a total favorite count of 4 or more. It uses a JOIN operation to connect the `users` and `posts` tables based on the `OwnerUserId` foreign key relationship."